main event: A white light, oscillating and slow moving, was observed for 10 minutes over Fort Monmouth, New Jersey on November 6, 1957.
interesting points: The sighting was made by military personnel.
The object was observed moving in a northeast direction.
An astro check with record and observatories indicated there was an Aurora Borealis display in the area at that time.
The report concludes that the sighting was most likely due to the Aurora Borealis.
Photographs of the object were included in the report.
sighted object: a white light, oscillating and slow moving
